article.description: — Dre Marin had 20 points as Southern Utah rolled past Bethesda 116-74 in a season opener on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Marin scores 20 as Southern Utah defeats Bethesda 116-74
article.linkText: Marin scores 20 as Southern Utah defeats Bethesda 116-74
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah -- — Dre Marin had 20 points as Southern Utah rolled past Bethesda 116-74 in a season opener on Tuesday night. Tevian Jones had 18 points for Southern Utah . John Knight III added 16 points. Aanen Moody had 15 points. Harrison Butler tied a career high with 13 rebounds to go with 6 points. Mark Carter had 18 points for the Flames. Daniel Estes added 13 points. Bethesda is an NCCAA member located in Anaheim, Calif. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
